<b>Subject:</b> Seems to me...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1140" TARGET=_self>Rogues in PvP</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>...that a Rogue/caster combo could be quite deadly. As an 8th level Druid I can root players, and a Rogue could simply sit behind them and melee (getting 2 or 3 backstabs off in the process) while I blast from afar. Anybody tried this yet?

<P>&gt; The last tester input I heard on Rogues in PvP is that they
<BR>&gt; don't work too well. I guess we will have to wait for more up to
<BR>&gt; date info to find out how vialble they are. As far as race-class
<BR>&gt; I prefer the Halfling Rogue, as the halfling has the racial
<BR>&gt; abilities to both hide and sneak (move silently), both essential
<BR>&gt; to the successfull thief/assassin.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
